                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                        Lieutenant General <persName type="to">Alvan C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-28">28 March
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82420. Reference your 373<note n="23" xml:id="d48fn23">March 27, <ref
                            target="#pg_603">p. 603</ref>.</note> Chou En-lai. Please advise me of
                    your estimate of situation in Kuomintang Party regarding good faith in carrying
                    out recommendations of PPC [<hi rend="italic">PCC</hi>].</p>
            </div>
        </body>
